lyrics:
[Verse]
Clocking systems, the workplace scene
Where characters emerge, all unique and mean
Dave Dempster loved the kids, didn't do his job
Tim Cotter knocked back Artna, a lowly engineer mob

Waldemar, lost in time, didn't know what day
Chris always moody, his vibes in disarray
Isaac's laughter echoed, heard from miles away
In this workplace circus, we all had our own say

[Chorus]
Clocking systems, where we unite and clash
Different personalities, a whirlwind clash
Oh, the workplace tales, the highs and lows we endure
Clocking systems, where we find our cure
